rComments: Terrible course, needs to be remade. The prof did not make it any better as he seemed careless at times.

Semester-long project with weekly deliverables plus labs and quizzes and assignments make the workload very heavy. Final was long but fair and he boosted the grades so don't listen to the ratings that were made right after the final in December 2020. He is a very good prof though and does everything to make his lectures interesting.

As other comments have said, yes the exam was rough but it was corrected in a fair manner. The class itself was demanding, but also rewarding. Mr. Dumond was a great prof and the class was well coordinated

The professor gave really interactive and interesting lectures during the online semester. This class is really stimulating and saved me from boredom this semester. There is a lot of work and you will want to help your teammates out to succeed. Beware of the final exam, it was very long and hard but he graded it with a lot of generosity !

This prof doesn't treat his students like actual people but robots instead. The workload was absurd. Every week there were multiple assignments due. He evaluated on too many things for a single class. Labs, Homework, quizes, midtem, oral presentations and a group projet . Avoid this class If you value your mental health at all.
Um he's a good teacher.

Dès le départ du cours, M. Dumond nous a clairement indiqué que le cours était un cours extrêmement demandant. Ce n'est pas comme si ce n'était pas indiqué que vous alliez souffrir. Travailler en équipe est essentiel. M. Dumond est un excellent professeur selon moi, il veut la réussite de ses étudiants. Ses slides sont organisées et interressantes.

On dirait qu'il s'en soucie, mais la classe doit être améliorée. Il semble qu'il ne sache pas que nous avons 4 à 5 autres classes d'ingénierie pour lesquelles nous devons également étudier. Jamais dans aucune de mes classes d'ingénierie je n'ai eu à faire la moitié du travail qui nous était confié dans cette classe.

Is the workload heavy? Of course. But he makes it very clear since the beginning that youre going to have to work very hard. If youre not willing to invest time and effort, the course is definitely not for you. His lecture presentations were some of the funnest and most engaging Ive had all semester and deeply cares for his students success.

This prof doesn't treat his students like actual people but robots instead. The workload was absurd. Every week there were multiple assignments due. He evaluated on too many things for a single class. Labs, Homework, quizes, midtem, oral presentations and a group projet (just to name a few) . Avoid this class If you value your mental health at all.

Patrick était lun de mes meilleurs profs à luniversité, ses slides étaient tellement bien faites et la présentation du cours en ligne était vraiment professionnelle, il utilisé un équipement spéciale et ces cours était toujours amusant. Le travail en groupe était horrible le test était long et difficile et les les labs nont pas de sens en ligne.

Tough grader, he was not quite intriguing as a prof. I found him quite difficult to follow. The whole class needs to be reconstructed rather than blasting bunch of 1 and 2 year student with the "reality of work". Maybe he can reduce less work load and start focusing more on small scale things. Would not recommend this prof avoid at all cost.
Terrible Professor, even with an A+ average currently (before exam) I have never seen such a terrible prof. Avoid at all costs.

Patrick dumond is hands down the worst prof i've ever had and ever will have. The workload is rediculous the final was rediculous we had to build a prototype during the final and the rest of the exam was completely undoable avoid at all costs!!!

Do you want to take a class that will make you regret going to uni, look no further. This prof will destroy you with 2-4 assignments/quizzes/presentations/labs. If you think your different and can possibly end this class with a 10, I wish you good luck, but I'm warning you that you will leave the class with PTSD from the amount of stress and work.
Do not ever take this prof
Terrible Prof, Avoid at all cost

Don't take this prof, worst prof in all of engineering, expects you to memorise 500 pages worth of slides and answer each question within 2 seconds. Class average is under 50% and he doesn't even change any format. I would rather drop out than ever take this terrible prof ever again.
Avoid at all cost

What is this teacher. Over 45 evaluations through the entire year. More than any class I have ever taken Even data structures and algorithms was an easier course and had less work to do (that class had weekly assignments which totaled to about 30 evaluations). There are even projects due after the final day of classes. Also the quizes  40% on all

Bruh gives you 20 minutes for 30 questions that "you're supposed to know" and the questions will be like a quote he said one time during a lecture. The last question of every test is worth at least 30% of the grade but you cant even get to it first because you cant go back on your questions for the tests. Completely ridiculous. Would NOT recommend

Worst prof I have ever had. Super cocky thinks hes superior to God because he has a PhD and will be cocky whenever you ask him a question. The class average on the exams we're under 30% yet he doesn't change the format and doesn't give any extra time. Worst of all on the final he makes you redo the project you did for the last 3 months in 2 hours.

The prof really simplified the material in the TB and explained it clearly. Don't get too worked up with all the tough problems in the TB since the exams are mostly easy and test your understanding of the concepts. If you keep up with the weekly DGD quizzes and HW, you should be prepared for the exams.

He goes through everything step-by-step in lectures, giving lots of examples along the way.  Always more than happy to explain what isn't clear. His course material is crystal clear, however, there is weekly homework and the exams are kinda tough. Very straightforward teaching style.  (Although he made me question if I was straight, myself).
Awesome prof! His lectures are very clear and structured. Examples are helpful. There's no reason not to like him.

The best prof I have had thus far. He goes through things slowly to help you understand. He writes all of his notes on the board so you can follow along with ease. I would highly recommend taking his class.

Dr. Dumond is a very organized professor. His lectures are clear. He always starts with a simple example and then does a more challenging one. He is very helpful in class, via email, and during office hours.  There are weekly quizzes in the DGDs, which are a major pain if you haven't had time to do the suggested exercises on your own.
Ce prof est un Alpha Male. Il explique très clairement et donne des excellentes explications et exemples. Si tu fait tout tes devoirs tu va passé.

Stay on top of the weekly homework, which really helps with studying for the midterm and final. Entertaining prof and gives great tips for solving problems. Stayed after every class to answer questions!

Lectures are clear and always have more than enough examples. There is weekly homework and quizzes but as long as you attend class and do practice questions it is fairly easy. Best prof this semester by far.

Omg this prof is the best. His notes are clear. He goes through examples for every type of question he could ask. His exams are easy to fair. He's super generous in his grading. Hot damn, if you get this prof, do yourself a favor and take him. Oh also the textbook is everything.

Patrick Dumond is a relatively above-average prof. Does many examples of the work in class, and the DGD's are full of examples, aswell as tests. There's weekly homework, but usually won't take more than one night to complete. Mr. Dumond does a good job at explaining the concepts, but is not the most interesting lecturer in the university.
makes you want to continue going to class
He is very organized and neat. He doesn't post his lectures online, so you will have a hard time catching up. BTW he is super hot :D
Very relatable guy, clear explanations. He gives you the impression he wants you to learn and in general my funest class.
Professor Dumond is amazing. He explains the content of this course very well and he is always available when you need help. Don't skip class tho, the explanations given in class are important ! :)

Patty is a true beauty. He's been in our shoes and understands the student prospective. This is definitely the hardest first year class but his clean explanations and his dedication to convey information clearly makes it easy. Down to earth guy, laid back, pretty relatable dude. Not ever worried to approach.

Its a shame the classroom was so subpar.   Excellent prof. Very clear, thorough with his lectures. If you have a question or misunderstanding, he will stop and reteach so that everyone can understand. Quizes and tests are straight forward. You do quizes regularly, so its very hard to get left behind. You are forced to learn the material. Excellent!
Good teacher overall but his TA's always give me a really hard time. No matter how good he teaches, the TA's give you super hard quizzes.

Très bon professeur, tout le monde comprend bien sa matière, il est toujours là pour nous aider si nous avons de la difficulté, grâce à lui j'aime la mécanique et il trouve le moyen de rendre sa matière intéréssante.

Notes on the board during lectures were very clear. If anyone didn't understand something, he would stop and explain the topic of difficulty in more detail. Well organized and always on time for class.
